<h2 id="section-top">Rheumatology</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=149">Taunton and Somerset NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address"><br/>01823 344823</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent792734f34bad4ecbb9a9b0e131542aae">
</div>
<p>The rheumatology department offices are based on the first floor of the Duchess building, near the Chapel.</p>
<p>The department provides both outpatient and inpatient care for patients presenting with rheumatic complaints with a particular emphasis on those with inflammatory disease, connective tissue disease including vasculitis. 97% of our patients on active follow up have inflammatory diseases. Patients with simple soft tissue rheumatism should be referred to the interface service, but if the history suggests an inflammatory component then these patients are best seen within the rheumatology department.</p>
<p>The department is currently staffed by four consultants: clinical lead Dr Cathy Laversuch, Dr Leslie Goh, Dr Luke Gompels, Dr Millicent Stone (part time), as well as a specialist registrar. There are two nurse specialists, Teresa Jewell and Kui-Leng Marrow, and a medical day unit sister, Judy Read.</p>
<p>There is an urgent access clinic and early arthritis clinic on Monday mornings and our specialist nurses also run a nurse led early arthritis clinic to see patients more frequently until their disease is controlled. Other clinics run in Taunton, Bridgwater, Minehead and Chard.</p>
<p>24 Hour Help Line: 01823 344093</p>
<p>If you have any queries you can call the 24 hour helpline, which is checked daily by our rheumatology nurse specialist.  It is for queries from patients, nurses and GPs. The 24 hour help line is now staffed by two rheumatology nurse specialists. Inpatient beds are on Triscombe Ward.</p>
<p>We see many of our patients on the medical day unit and run injection clinics with and without sedation. Some patients with small joint osteoarthritis unresponsive to simple analgesia and topical therapies may benefit from local injections in the inflammatory phase.</p>
<p>Combined clinics are held with our colleagues in orthopaedics and respiratory medicine and with Professor Denton for patients with scleroderma.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
